WEBVTT

1
00:00:16.058 --> 00:00:17.768
- What's up. Ghost Rider?
- You good?

2
00:00:17.851 --> 00:00:18.977
Never better.

3
00:00:19.061 --> 00:00:20.812
OK. kids. bye-bye time.

4
00:00:20.896 --> 00:00:23.023
Thanks for the trip
down memory lane.

5
00:00:23.106 --> 00:00:24.441
Um. where's Evans?

6
00:00:24.525 --> 00:00:26.735
Uh. I think
she's by the family room.

7
00:00:26.818 --> 00:00:28.320
She is.

8
00:00:28.403 --> 00:00:29.821
Hey. hey. hey.
where are you going?

9
00:00:29.905 --> 00:00:31.365
I'm not gonna scan
all this by myself.

10
00:00:31.448 --> 00:00:32.950
Cruz has a question
on my cellulitis.

11
00:00:33.033 --> 00:00:34.576
- I'll be right back.
- You better.

12
00:00:34.660 --> 00:00:35.827
- Two minutes tops.
- Where's Mel?

13
00:00:35.911 --> 00:00:37.329
Where's Donnie?

14
00:00:37.412 --> 00:00:38.789
- They should be helping you.
- I don't know.

15
00:00:38.872 --> 00:00:40.541
OK. day shift. listen up.

16
00:00:40.624 --> 00:00:42.668
We're doing really well.
but we still got a ways to go.

17
00:00:42.751 --> 00:00:44.795
And nobody's going home
until all these paper charts

18
00:00:44.878 --> 00:00:46.505
are digitized. including me.

19
00:00:46.588 --> 00:00:48.465
And then we're free
to celebrate our freedom?

20
00:00:48.549 --> 00:00:49.550
Exactly.

21
00:00:49.633 --> 00:00:50.801
Well. can you kick some ass

22
00:00:50.884 --> 00:00:51.969
and get the staff to hurry up

23
00:00:52.052 --> 00:00:53.136
on the EHR home pages?

24
00:00:53.220 --> 00:00:54.846
Where are Larry and Antoine?

25
00:00:54.930 --> 00:00:56.139
Antoine's fighting
on the phone

26
00:00:56.223 --> 00:00:57.516
with his girlfriend outside.

27
00:00:57.599 --> 00:01:00.310
And Larry's on a cafeteria run.

28
00:01:00.394 --> 00:01:02.854
Yeah. that tracks.

29
00:01:02.938 --> 00:01:04.982
We've got five patients
in beds waiting to be seen.

30
00:01:05.065 --> 00:01:06.984
How do you want to play this--
man to man or zone?

31
00:01:07.067 --> 00:01:08.443
The zone.

32
00:01:08.527 --> 00:01:10.112
Have Cruz and Ellis split up
the new five.

33
00:01:10.195 --> 00:01:11.488
You take North and Central.

34
00:01:11.572 --> 00:01:13.198
- I'll take South and Trauma.
- Cool.

35
00:01:13.282 --> 00:01:14.283
Want to switch at 1:00 AM?

36
00:01:14.366 --> 00:01:15.409
Why?

37
00:01:15.492 --> 00:01:16.618
Variety is the spice of life.

38
00:01:16.702 --> 00:01:18.036
I thought that was garlic.

39
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.039
Oh. sorry.

40
00:01:21.123 --> 00:01:22.958
I told you I'd be fast.

41
00:01:23.041 --> 00:01:25.043
OK. let's do this
and get out of here.

42
00:01:25.127 --> 00:01:26.169
What's the hurry?

43
00:01:26.253 --> 00:01:27.421
Got some hay to pitch?

44
00:01:27.504 --> 00:01:28.839
Ha.

45
00:01:30.424 --> 00:01:32.092
- Oh. shoot.
- What?

46
00:01:32.175 --> 00:01:34.720
Uh. my ID badge is missing.

47
00:01:34.803 --> 00:01:35.762
Oh. no.
The one you just got?

48
00:01:35.846 --> 00:01:37.139
How'd you lose it?

49
00:01:37.222 --> 00:01:38.140
I don't know.
It must have come off.

50
00:01:38.223 --> 00:01:39.474
Classic.

51
00:01:39.558 --> 00:01:40.851
Hope you remember
your login and password.

52
00:01:40.934 --> 00:01:42.019
OK. Retrace your steps.

53
00:01:42.102 --> 00:01:43.478
Where'd you have it last?

54
00:01:43.562 --> 00:01:46.148
Uh. I was with Ogilvie
in the Ambulance Bay.

55
00:01:46.231 --> 00:01:48.317
Not with Colonel Mustard
in the library?

56
00:01:48.400 --> 00:01:50.360
Who's--what?

57
00:01:50.444 --> 00:01:51.612
No.

58
00:01:52.946 --> 00:01:55.282
The boy has no clue.

59
00:01:59.703 --> 00:02:01.705
Please don't do that.

60
00:02:01.788 --> 00:02:03.457
Oh. ma'am. I gotta go.

61
00:02:03.540 --> 00:02:06.168
I sit here any longer.
I'm gonna get bedsores.

62
00:02:08.378 --> 00:02:11.298
I--I'm supposed to get
some CT results.

63
00:02:11.381 --> 00:02:13.759
Any idea how much longer
that's gonna be?

64
00:02:13.842 --> 00:02:16.219
Shouldn't be much longer.

65
00:02:16.303 --> 00:02:18.805
Where's that Nurse Vivi?

66
00:02:18.889 --> 00:02:20.515
You don't want any of that.

67
00:02:20.599 --> 00:02:22.768
- No?
- No. she's out of your league.

68
00:02:22.851 --> 00:02:24.728
What league do you think
I play in?

69
00:02:24.811 --> 00:02:27.522
Uh. old timer's night.

70
00:02:27.606 --> 00:02:29.191
Yeah. you're probably right.

71
00:02:29.274 --> 00:02:32.319
But some teams still appreciate
a veteran presence.

72
00:02:32.402 --> 00:02:34.529
Well. don't say
I didn't warn you.

73
00:02:34.613 --> 00:02:36.281
You are here for your heart.
after all.

74
00:02:36.365 --> 00:02:37.783
My heart's been
broken before.

75
00:02:37.866 --> 00:02:39.326
What's one more time?

76
00:02:39.409 --> 00:02:41.411
Uh. she's engaged
to a jujitsu instructor.

77
00:02:41.495 --> 00:02:43.121
With a bang.
not a whimper. baby.

78
00:02:44.623 --> 00:02:46.208
And it's a cool bath
a couple times a day

79
00:02:46.291 --> 00:02:48.752
for two days. followed by
aloe vera to your skin.

80
00:02:48.835 --> 00:02:50.087
OK. that's it?

81
00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:52.339
And sunscreen in your future.

82
00:02:52.422 --> 00:02:55.342
No. I'm never going outside
ever again.

83
00:02:55.425 --> 00:02:58.804
I wouldn't swear off the sun
entirely. you know?

84
00:02:58.887 --> 00:03:01.306
But like most things.
moderation.

85
00:03:01.390 --> 00:03:02.599
Hey. we're getting
kind of shorthanded

86
00:03:02.683 --> 00:03:03.975
scanning charts out here.

87
00:03:04.059 --> 00:03:05.352
When you finish.
can you come lend a hand?

88
00:03:05.435 --> 00:03:06.436
Yeah. happy to.

89
00:03:06.520 --> 00:03:07.521
Thank you.

90
00:03:09.564 --> 00:03:11.441
And by happy to.
I mean there is nothing

91
00:03:11.525 --> 00:03:13.193
I would rather do less.

92
00:03:13.276 --> 00:03:15.821
They keep you pretty busy.

93
00:03:15.904 --> 00:03:19.950
Yeah. and today has brought
some new challenges.

94
00:03:20.033 --> 00:03:21.201
This is really putting a crimp

95
00:03:21.284 --> 00:03:23.495
in my 4th of July
evening plans.

96
00:03:23.578 --> 00:03:25.997
You're going to see
the fireworks?

97
00:03:26.081 --> 00:03:29.418
Uh. no. I was gonna maybe
meet up with this guy.

98
00:03:29.501 --> 00:03:31.002
though that's sounding
less appealing

99
00:03:31.086 --> 00:03:33.505
than the three Bs
at this point.

100
00:03:33.588 --> 00:03:35.132
The three Bs?

101
00:03:36.174 --> 00:03:38.510
Book. bath. and bed.

102
00:03:38.593 --> 00:03:40.971
College kid with mono
and hemorrhagic tonsils.

103
00:03:41.054 --> 00:03:42.681
admit med-surge or observation?

104
00:03:42.764 --> 00:03:43.765
Uh. observation.

105
00:03:43.849 --> 00:03:45.183
Bleeding stopped with TXA.

106
00:03:45.267 --> 00:03:46.601
She's had steroids.
so should be

107
00:03:46.685 --> 00:03:47.936
ready for discharge
in the morning.

108
00:03:48.019 --> 00:03:49.688
Cool.

109
00:03:49.771 --> 00:03:51.440
How was your first shift back?

110
00:03:51.523 --> 00:03:54.109
Uh. slow start.
finding my rhythm.

111
00:03:55.444 --> 00:03:57.446
You a little rusty.
Rusty James?

112
00:03:57.529 --> 00:03:59.865
Now you won't have Motorcycle
Boy to big brother you.

113
00:03:59.948 --> 00:04:01.491
Is that a "Rumble Fish"
reference?

114
00:04:01.575 --> 00:04:02.951
Sure is.

115
00:04:03.034 --> 00:04:05.579
And Robby is my big brother
in this analogy?

116
00:04:05.662 --> 00:04:06.830
Bingo.

117
00:04:06.913 --> 00:04:07.956
Yeah. I wouldn't say
he's been

118
00:04:08.039 --> 00:04:09.833
looking out for me exactly.

119
00:04:09.916 --> 00:04:11.293
I think he'd probably prefer

120
00:04:11.376 --> 00:04:13.003
