straight to Trauma 2.

263
00:09:21.144 --> 00:09:22.395
What is his story?

264
00:09:22.479 --> 00:09:23.772
Bottle to the face.
strong vitals.

265
00:09:23.855 --> 00:09:24.898
12-centimeter facial lac.

266
00:09:24.981 --> 00:09:26.399
Yeah. where do you want us?

267
00:09:26.483 --> 00:09:28.735
- North 4 just got cleaned.
- To the North.

268
00:09:28.818 --> 00:09:31.029
Abbot. single MVA en route.
Five away.

269
00:09:31.112 --> 00:09:32.906
Olive. can you find Robby
and Al-Hashimi?

270
00:09:32.989 --> 00:09:34.282
We may need a couple more hands

271
00:09:34.365 --> 00:09:35.742
until we get caught up
with these two.

272
00:09:35.825 --> 00:09:36.868
Sir. we are gonna get you
more pain meds...

273
00:09:36.951 --> 00:09:38.328
It hurts.

274
00:09:38.411 --> 00:09:39.621
But you need to shut
your fucking mouth.

275
00:09:39.704 --> 00:09:41.122
The acronym is SMART.

276
00:09:41.206 --> 00:09:43.416
Single Maintenance
and Reliever Therapy.

277
00:09:43.500 --> 00:09:46.503
It's one inhaler that combines
an inhaled corticosteroid

278
00:09:46.586 --> 00:09:49.172
with a fast-acting.
long-lasting beta agonist.

279
00:09:49.255 --> 00:09:51.841
That's fancy talk
for an anti-inflammatory

280
00:09:51.925 --> 00:09:54.677
and a lung muscle relaxer
all rolled into one.

281
00:09:54.761 --> 00:09:57.097
But it's $400.
And without Medicaid--

282
00:09:57.180 --> 00:09:59.057
We can help you look
into coverage options.

283
00:09:59.140 --> 00:10:00.850
- Thank you.
- Of course.

284
00:10:00.934 --> 00:10:02.977
Grady should feel worlds
better in a few hours.

285
00:10:03.061 --> 00:10:05.063
Thank you.

286
00:10:05.146 --> 00:10:09.317
So what are my chances
of getting off the table alive?

287
00:10:09.400 --> 00:10:11.945
Once you're cleared by
the heart and lung specialists

288
00:10:12.028 --> 00:10:16.157
next week. chances of death
are low. like 1% or 2%.

289
00:10:16.241 --> 00:10:18.660
And how long would I
be in surgery for?

290
00:10:18.743 --> 00:10:21.412
Between three and five hours.

291
00:10:21.496 --> 00:10:22.622
Jeez.

292
00:10:22.705 --> 00:10:24.082
It's long...

293
00:10:24.165 --> 00:10:27.502
Because they have to stop
your heart.

294
00:10:27.585 --> 00:10:30.713
You will be on a heart-lung
bypass machine.

295
00:10:30.797 --> 00:10:33.550
which will be circulating
your blood while they repair

296
00:10:33.633 --> 00:10:35.718
the aneurysm with the graft.

297
00:10:35.802 --> 00:10:37.887
Well. what's the graft
made out of?

298
00:10:37.971 --> 00:10:42.100
A synthetic fabric called
Dacron. super strong.

299
00:10:42.183 --> 00:10:43.434
OK.

300
00:10:43.518 --> 00:10:45.478
New hoses. new gaskets.

301
00:10:45.562 --> 00:10:47.272
Then what happens
after surgery?

302
00:10:47.355 --> 00:10:49.649
You will be in the hospital
for about a week.

303
00:10:49.732 --> 00:10:51.526
No work for eight weeks
after that.

304
00:10:51.609 --> 00:10:52.944
no strenuous activity.

305
00:10:53.027 --> 00:10:56.322
no lifting anything
over 5 pounds.

306
00:10:56.406 --> 00:10:59.492
How am I supposed
to take a piss?

307
00:10:59.576 --> 00:11:01.369
Nice.

308
00:11:04.539 --> 00:11:07.709
And how long till
I'm back up to full speed?

309
00:11:07.792 --> 00:11:10.962
Three months. maybe more
like six. given your age.

310
00:11:13.047 --> 00:11:14.841
And if I don't
get the surgery?

311
00:11:17.302 --> 00:11:19.762
50% chance of death
within 12 months

312
00:11:19.846 --> 00:11:21.347
if the aneurysm ruptures.

313
00:11:22.557 --> 00:11:25.518
What would I feel
if it ruptured?

314
00:11:27.687 --> 00:11:30.106
Some chest pain.
maybe some shortness of breath

315
00:11:30.190 --> 00:11:32.650
for about a minute before you
passed out from blood loss.

316
00:11:32.734 --> 00:11:34.611
And then?

317
00:11:34.694 --> 00:11:35.945
The big fade out?

318
00:11:36.029 --> 00:11:38.740
Roll the credits.

319
00:11:44.537 --> 00:11:46.623
Quite the coin flip.

320
00:11:46.706 --> 00:11:48.958
No coin flip.
This has to happen.

321
00:11:49.042 --> 00:11:51.711
But I do worry that you are not
gonna make your appointments

322
00:11:51.794 --> 00:11:54.547
or follow your aftercare
instructions if I'm not here.

323
00:11:54.631 --> 00:11:56.382
Sorry. Robby.
Abbot asked for me to grab you

324
00:11:56.466 --> 00:11:57.675
for an MVA on route.

325
00:12:00.261 --> 00:12:01.512
Do what you gotta do. man.

326
00:12:01.596 --> 00:12:03.264
I gotta sit with this
for a minute.

327
00:12:05.266 --> 00:12:07.894
You go ahead and get dressed.

328
00:12:07.977 --> 00:12:09.520
I'll come back.

329
00:12:37.340 --> 00:12:39.259
Monica got an ICU bed
upstairs

330
00:12:39.342 --> 00:12:41.719
so we can take Orlando up now.

331
00:12:41.803 --> 00:12:43.805
- We'll prep him for transfer.
- Thanks. hon.

332
00:12:43.888 --> 00:12:45.640
We need this room again
in a minute.

333
00:12:57.068 --> 00:12:58.111
All good?

334
00:12:58.194 --> 00:13:00.655
Uh. totally.

335
00:13:00.738 --> 00:13:03.116
Uh. totally?

336
00:13:03.199 --> 00:13:05.493
Look. once more.
I feel compelled

337
00:13:05.576 --> 00:13:09.831
to offer some unasked for
and probably unwanted advice.

338
00:13:10.999 --> 00:13:13.334
Javadi wasn't making
a TikTok video.

339
00:13:13.418 --> 00:13:14.877
She's been posting about Jesse.

340
00:13:14.961 --> 00:13:17.046
trying to find someone
who knows where he is.

341
00:13:17.130 --> 00:13:18.381
Ah.

342
00:13:19.549 --> 00:13:22.260
And even if she were
making one of her videos.

343
00:13:22.343 --> 00:13:23.469
you ever watched one?

344
00:13:23.553 --> 00:13:24.971
No.

345
00:13:25.054 --> 00:13:26.681
No. my account was suspended

346
00:13:26.764 --> 00:13:29.183
for erotically seditious
content.

347
00:13:29.267 --> 00:13:31.144
Well. they're not
what you think.

348
00:13:31.227 --> 00:13:32.520
They're actually kind of cool.

349
00:13:32.603 --> 00:13:34.647
It's like this badass
self-care.

350
00:13:34.731 --> 00:13:36.607
Huh.

351
00:13:36.691 --> 00:13:38.067
OK. that is it.

352
00:13:38.151 --> 00:13:39.569
I'm going to bury myself
in charting

353
00:13:39.652 --> 00:13:40.820
and try to dig my way out.

354
00:13:40.903 --> 00:13:42.113
Edith Lynch. 46.

355
00:13:42.196 --> 00:13:43.614
right-sided chest pain
for an hour.

356
00:13:43.698 --> 00:13:44.949
No cardiac history.

357
00:13:45.033 --> 00:13:46.534
minimal relief
from sublingual nitro.

358
00:13:46.617 --> 00:13:48.077
- no STEMI on the 12-lead.
- Dana?

359
00:13:48.161 --> 00:13:50.330
South 15.

360
00:13:50.413 --> 00:13:51.956
Hi. Edith.
I'm Dr. Al-Hashimi.

361
00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:53.916
We'll be taking care
of you today.

362
00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:56.294
Absent lung sliding
on the right.

363
00:13:56.377 --> 00:13:57.628
I could have told you that
from here.

364
00:13:57.712 --> 00:13:59.088
God bless America.

365
00:13:59.172 --> 00:14:00.798
Hemodynamically stable.

366
00:14:00.882 --> 00:14:02.508
I'll put in a 20 French.
and then right up to the OR.

367
00:14:02.592 --> 00:14:04.218
Whoa. whoa. whoa!
Hold on!

368
00:14:04.302 --> 00:14:05.428
I need surgery?

369
00:14:05.511 --> 00:14:06.888
Sir. you have
a collapsed lung.

370
00:14:06.971 --> 00:14:08.181
We need to put a tube
in your chest to see

371
00:14:08.264 --> 00:14:09.599
how much internal bleeding
there is.

372
00:14:09.682 --> 00:14:11.184
Oh. come on. man.
just pull it out!

373
00:14:11.267 --> 00:14:12.685
- Nuh-uh.
- No.

374
00:14:12.769 --> 00:14:14.771
OK. everyone knows
what to do here. right?

375
00:14:14.854 --> 00:14:17.607
We're gonna take this at a nice
slow pace. moving together.

376
00:14:17.690 --> 00:14:19.150
If anyone has an issue.
speak up.

377
00:14:19.233 --> 00:14:21.235
There are a lot
of moving parts here.

378
00:14:21.319 --> 00:14:22.904
Are they going up
to ICU finally?

379
00:14:22.987 --> 00:14:23.905
- Yes.
- Great.

380
00:14:23.988 --> 00:14:25.406
How you doing?

381
00:14:25.490 --> 00:14:26.866
Is that a trick question.
or--

382
00:14:26.949 --> 00:14:29.035
Not intended to be. no.

383
00:14:29.118 --> 00:14:30.495
Then not great.

384
00:14:30.578 --> 00:14:32.413
This one got past me.

385
00:14:32.497 --> 00:14:35.124
Well. listen. you tried
to find a viable payment plan.

386
00:14:35.208 --> 00:14:36.793
You tried to keep him here.

387
00:14:36.876 --> 00:14:38.753
You even tried to give him
a goodie bag. but he left.

388
00:14:38.836 --> 00:14:39.921
I'm not sure what else
you could have done.

389
00:14:40.004 --> 00:14:41.631
Been more persuasive.

390
00:14:41.714 --> 00:14:44.717
This was the patient's call--
his life. his mistake.

391
00:14:44.801 --> 00:14:46.928
What mistake.
getting diabetes?

392
00:14:47.011 --> 00:14:49.639
Not picking a higher spot
to jump from.

393
00:14:59.941 --> 00:15:01.692
History of hyperlipidemia.

394
00:15:01.776 --> 00:15:03.945
an hour of substernal
chest pain.

395
00:15:04.028 --> 00:15:06.572
minimal relief with nitro
and 4 of MS.

396
00:15:06.656 --> 00:15:08.616
EKG is negative for STEMI.

397
00:15:08.699 --> 00:15:12.912
Heart score is 4. gave 324
milligrams of chewable aspirin.

398
00:15:12.995 --> 00:15:14.664
admit for new onset angina.

399
00:15:14.747 --> 00:15:16.666
Don't mind me.
I'm just passing through.

400
00:15:16.749 --> 00:15:18.251
Seemed like you wanted
an update.

401
00:15:18.334 --> 00:15:19.710
Well. as long as you feel
like you got it covered.

402
00:15:19.794 --> 00:15:21.170
I do.

403
00:15:21.254 --> 00:15:22.880
Go ahead and repeat
the 12-lead.

404
00:15:22.964 --> 00:15:24.465
Since I'm here. I did want
to ask you about something

405
00:15:24.549 --> 00:15:25.758
I observed earlier.

406
00:15:25.842 --> 00:15:27.093
Oh. you gotta be
fucking kidding me.

407
00:15:27.176 --> 00:15:28.594
What?

408
00:15:28.678 --> 00:15:30.304
Look where these
anterior leads are placed.

409
00:15:30.388 --> 00:15:32.473
They're way too low.

410
00:15:32.557 --> 00:15:33.558
Holy shit!
What's happening?

411
00:15:33.641 --> 00:15:35.518
Mrs. Lynch?
V-tach!

412
00:15:35.601 --> 00:15:36.727
No pulse.

413
00:15:36.811 --> 00:15:39.188
Charge to 200.

414
00:15:39.272 --> 00:15:40.523
Charged.

415
00:15:40.606 --> 00:15:42.733
And clear.

416
00:15:42.817 --> 00:15:44.694
OK. Normal sinus.

417
00:15:44.777 --> 00:15:46.988
Strong pulse. Cycle a BP.

418
00:15:48.906 --> 00:15:50.491
Let's repeat
that EKG. please.

419
00:15:50.575 --> 00:15:52.660
Put the leads
in the right fucking place.

420
00:15:52.743 --> 00:15:55.288
- Who were the medics on this?
- Bosco and Otero.

421
00:15:55.371 --> 00:15:56.998
Bosco and Otero.

422
00:15:57.081 --> 00:15:59.876
OK. Bosco and Otero.

423
00:15:59.959 --> 00:16:01.669
See you on Monday.

424
00:16:01.752 --> 00:16:03.546
May your night go smoother
than my day.

425
00:16:03.629 --> 00:16:05.173
Happy 4th.

426
00:16:05.256 --> 00:16:07.049
Heard it's been crazy.
They shut down when ICE came.

427
00:16:07.133 --> 00:16:09.302
Separate events.
Get someone else to explain.

428
00:16:09.385 --> 00:16:10.595
I'm going home.

429
00:16:10.678 --> 00:16:12.763
Damn. what is that?
That smells good.

430
00:16:12.847 --> 00:16:14.015
Food from home.

431
00:16:14.098 --> 00:16:15.641
I can't do the cafeteria.

432
00:16:15.725 --> 00:16:17.143
Oh. you gotta give me
that recipe.

433
00:16:17.226 --> 00:16:18.853
- I'm going home.
- Get home safe.

434
00:16:18.936 --> 00:16:19.896
Mm-hmm.

435
00:16:23.274 --> 00:16:25.485
- Hey.
- Hey.

436
00:16:25.568 --> 00:16:27.236
- I'm starving.
- Of course.

437
00:16:27.320 --> 00:16:29.447
I will give you $20
for whatever that smell is.

438
00:16:29.530 --> 00:16:30.823
I'll give you some.

439
00:16:30.907 --> 00:16:32.033
- I made too much anyway.
- Thank you.

440
00:16:32.116 --> 00:16:33.201
- Just give me a sec.
- Yeah.

441
00:16:33.284 --> 00:16:34.660
How can I help you?

442
00:16:34.744 --> 00:16:35.745
My granddad just about
cut his hand off

443
00:16:35.828 --> 00:16:37.121
with a tug-of-war rope.

444
00:16:37.205 --> 00:16:39.832
Hi. I--I remember you
from earlier.

445
00:16:39.916 --> 00:16:41.000
You're having
a family reunion. right?

446
00:16:41.083 --> 00:16:42.251
Yeah.

447
00:16:42.335 --> 00:16:43.753
Is your hand
actively bleeding?

448
00:16:43.836 --> 00:16:46.756
Oh. not so bad.
Here. take a look.

449
00:16:46.839 --> 00:16:48.132
Mateo. one to come
straight back!

450
00:16:48.216 --> 00:16:50.176
- Oh. my God.
- Cover that up. please.

451
00:16:50.259 --> 00:16:52.178
I'll need to get
a demographics from you.

452
00:16:52.261 --> 00:16:53.763
You got them already.

453
00:16:53.846 --> 00:16:55.598
Hansens been in and out
of here all day long.

454
00:16:55.681 --> 00:16:56.891
How did this happen?

455
00:16:56.974 --> 00:16:58.100
He had the rope
wrapped around his hand.

456
00:16:58.184 --> 00:16:59.560
cut through it like a machete.

457
00:16:59.644 --> 00:17:01.395
Have a seat. sir.
I'll take you right back.

458
00:17:01.479 --> 00:17:04.273
And how would you rate your
pain on a scale from 1 to 10?

459
00:17:04.357 --> 00:17:07.235
Oh. it's not too bad
on account of my sugars.

460
00:17:08.361 --> 00:17:10.738
With his diabetes.
his sensation's a little off.

461
00:17:10.821 --> 00:17:11.739
Yeah.

462
00:17:11.822 --> 00:17:12.865
After you.

463
00:17:12.949 --> 00:17:13.866
Thanks.

464
00:17:13.950 --> 00:17:16.118
Ow.
What the fuck?

465
00:17:16.202 --> 00:17:17.787
Trigeminal nerve is good.

466
00:17:17.870 --> 00:17:20.081
Shit!
You gonna fix me or torture me?

467
00:17:20.164 --> 00:17:22.375
Ooh. ouch!

468
00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:24.502
Yeah. I need
to call plastics.

469
00:17:24.585 --> 00:17:27.129
I called a "kiss off the two.
off the rail."

470
00:17:27.213 --> 00:17:29.131
Fucker said I didn't call it.

471
00:17:29.215 --> 00:17:32.093
Okay. yes. it was a bit noisy.
The fourth is Styx night.

472
00:17:32.176 --> 00:17:33.886
But I called it.
I have witnesses.

473
00:17:33.970 --> 00:17:35.263
Styx. the band?

474
00:17:35.346 --> 00:17:36.264
Yeah.

475
00:17:36.347 --> 00:17:37.431
Ah. love Styx.

476
00:17:37.515 --> 00:17:38.766
I never heard of them.

477
00:17:38.849 --> 00:17:40.685
You never heard of Styx?

478
00:17:40.768 --> 00:17:41.936
"Mr. Roboto"?

479
00:17:42.019 --> 00:17:44.522
My Spotify age isn't 62.

480
00:17:44.605 --> 00:17:47.149
"Come Sail Away"?
"Lady"? "Babe"?

481
00:17:48.609 --> 00:17:50.945
Yeah. maybe best
if you don't talk.

482
00:17:51.028 --> 00:17:53.614
Looks like there's some sort
of foreign body in there.

483
00:17:53.698 --> 00:17:55.241
Mm-hmm.

484
00:17:55.324 --> 00:17:56.742
Are you OK?

485
00:17:56.826 --> 00:17:58.786
Yeah. it's just
an awkward position.

486
00:17:58.869 --> 00:18:00.955
Go home.
Rest. heat. ice.

487
00:18:01.038 --> 00:18:02.206
Yeah. no. no. I know.

488
00:18:02.290 --> 00:18:04.041
I'm just waiting
for things to slow down.

489
00:18:04.125 --> 00:18:06.544
You know. express trains
don't stop at your station.

490
00:18:07.795 --> 00:18:09.880
You just gotta jump.

491
00:18:09.964 --> 00:18:11.007
What is that?

492
00:18:11.090 --> 00:18:12.258
Heineken?

493
00:18:12.341 --> 00:18:13.259
Moosehead?

494
00:18:13.342 --> 00:18:14.719
Oh.

495
00:18:14.802 --> 00:18:17.388
From the glass-lined tanks
of Old Latrobe.

496
00:18:17.471 --> 00:18:19.390
Ah. Rolling Rock.

497
00:18:19.473 --> 00:18:20.474
Nice.

498
00:18:25.104 --> 00:18:26.814
She's had four of morphine.

499
00:18:26.897 --> 00:18:28.274
How's the pain?

500
00:18:28.357 --> 00:18:29.567
Down to an 8.

501
00:18:29.650 --> 00:18:31.027
There it is. lateral STEMI.

502
00:18:31.110 --> 00:18:32.278
OK. call it in.

503
00:18:32.361 --> 00:18:33.946
The leads were too low
to catch it?

504
00:18:34.030 --> 00:18:35.489
Yeah. it's not the first time
it's happened.

505
00:18:35.573 --> 00:18:37.033
You get a male medic
who's more concerned about

506
00:18:37.116 --> 00:18:38.576
getting sued or a complaint
for undoing a bra.

507
00:18:38.659 --> 00:18:40.036
You see these
anterior leads here?

508
00:18:40.119 --> 00:18:41.454
Code STEMI. South 15.

509
00:18:41.537 --> 00:18:42.788
Edith. you're having
a heart attack

510
00:18:42.872 --> 00:18:44.290
from a blockage in the artery

511
00:18:44.373 --> 00:18:46.000
that brings oxygen
to your heart muscle.

512
00:18:46.083 --> 00:18:48.210
- If we get you to the--
- Lateral STEMI. V-tach arrest.

513
00:18:48.294 --> 00:18:50.171
Got her back after one shock.
She needs the cath lab.

514
00:18:50.254 --> 00:18:51.881
- And serious heart damage.
- Oh. my God.

515
00:18:51.964 --> 00:18:54.634
- You're going to be OK.
- Hello. I'm Dr. Cruz.

516
00:18:54.717 --> 00:18:56.344
And I'm Dr. Shen.
How are you feeling?

517
00:18:56.427 --> 00:18:57.762
I'm really scared.

518
00:18:57.845 --> 00:18:59.472
We've got you.
Anything else?

519
00:18:59.555 --> 00:19:01.557
Uh. like I got kicked
in the chest.

520
00:19:01.641 --> 00:19:03.267
Normal after
a shock to the heart.

521
00:19:03.351 --> 00:19:05.019
- Family?
- Yeah. husband's en route.

522
00:19:05.102 --> 00:19:06.771
Leave the defib pads on
and take her up in a minute.

523
00:19:06.854 --> 00:19:08.147
I'm gonna chaperone
a nerve block real quick.

524
00:19:08.230 --> 00:19:09.231
Go.

525
00:19:11.275 --> 00:19:12.902
Where's Dr. Al-Hashimi?

526
00:19:12.985 --> 00:19:14.820
She was just here.

527
00:19:24.246 --> 00:19:26.374
Hello. everyone.
I'm Dr. Shen.

528
00:19:26.457 --> 00:19:28.209
Heard a rumor someone
needed a nerve block.

529
00:19:28.292 --> 00:19:29.877
I'm guessing that's you.

530
00:19:29.960 --> 00:19:31.921
Probably so. although.

531
00:19:32.004 --> 00:19:33.506
you know.
I don't have much pain.

532
00:19:33.589 --> 00:19:35.591
I guess it's my diabetes.

533
00:19:35.675 --> 00:19:39.136
We still need to numb you up
to do a proper deep clean.

534
00:19:39.220 --> 00:19:41.055
You guys do
whatever you gotta do.

535
00:19:41.138 --> 00:19:43.516
Three shots. median.
ulnar. and radial.

536
00:19:43.599 --> 00:19:45.393
2 grams of Ancef.
100 milligrams of Gent

537
00:19:45.476 --> 00:19:46.602
for gram-negative coverage.

538
00:19:46.686 --> 00:19:47.978
How'd you do this?

539
00:19:48.062 --> 00:19:50.648
Oh. a family reunion
tug-of-war.

540
00:19:50.731 --> 00:19:52.817
I wrapped the rope around
my hand for better grip.

541
00:19:52.900 --> 00:19:55.861
And when we fell down. those
bastards just kept pulling.

542
00:19:55.945 --> 00:19:57.405
Dirty.

543
00:19:57.488 --> 00:19:59.949
Nah. it's just--
just the way we play.

544
00:20:02.827 --> 00:20:04.245
Michael. you got a second?

545
00:20:04.328 --> 00:20:05.830
Uh. not really. no.

546
00:20:05.913 --> 00:20:07.623
Well. how about
showing me a little respect

547
00:20:07.707 --> 00:20:09.792
and finding one?

548
00:20:09.875 --> 00:20:10.918
Sorry. Caleb.

549
00:20:11.001 --> 00:20:12.420
Are you feeling disrespected?

550
00:20:12.503 --> 00:20:14.422
Given that you've been
actively blowing me off

551
00:20:14.505 --> 00:20:16.048
all day. yeah.
maybe a little bit.

552
00:20:16.132 --> 00:20:17.466
But I have a thick skin.

553
00:20:18.843 --> 00:20:20.386
What can I do for you?

554
00:20:20.469 --> 00:20:23.305
"Should have found
a higher place to jump from."

555
00:20:23.389 --> 00:20:25.683
It's an interesting diagnosis.
Doctor.

556
00:20:29.645 --> 00:20:31.272
No pithy retort?

557
00:20:31.355 --> 00:20:33.315
Yeah. I didn't think so.

558
00:20:33.399 --> 00:20:35.609
Uh. I just came to say goodbye.

559
00:20:35.693 --> 00:20:37.319
I'm leaving soon.

560
00:20:37.403 --> 00:20:39.029
I know you are too.

561
00:20:40.448 --> 00:20:42.032
Yes.

562
00:20:43.409 --> 00:20:45.661
Keep my number handy.
just in case. huh?

563
00:20:45.745 --> 00:20:47.663
Yes. I promise I will.

564
00:20:47.747 --> 00:20:48.956
Thank you. Caleb.

565
00:20:51.459 --> 00:20:53.669
We're gonna give you one
Diflucan pill to take home.

566
00:20:53.753 --> 00:20:56.547
Take it in three days
if your symptoms persist.

567
00:20:56.630 --> 00:20:58.340
How do I get there?

568
00:20:58.424 --> 00:20:59.759
Where's that?

569
00:20:59.842 --> 00:21:01.427
Home.

570
00:21:01.510 --> 00:21:02.720
Do you know where you live?

571
00:21:02.803 --> 00:21:04.638
Of course I do. It's not far.

572
00:21:04.722 --> 00:21:07.016
But I don't have
a way to get there.

573
00:21:08.267 --> 00:21:09.852
How'd you get here?

574
00:21:09.935 --> 00:21:12.188
My--my neighbor Gwen
dropped me off.

575
00:21:12.271 --> 00:21:14.523
but she can't drive at night.

576
00:21:14.607 --> 00:21:17.234
We could call you
an Uber or a taxi.

577
00:21:17.318 --> 00:21:19.904
I don't have any money.

578
00:21:19.987 --> 00:21:21.572
Excuse me.

579
00:21:21.655 --> 00:21:23.157
Can I help?

580
00:21:23.240 --> 00:21:24.867
Mrs. Clymer has
been discharged.

581
00:21:24.950 --> 00:21:25.868
but has no way home.

582
00:21:25.951 --> 00:21:26.911
I'm so sorry.

583
00:21:26.994 --> 00:21:27.912
I don't mean to be a burden.

584
00:21:27.995 --> 00:21:29.288
No burden at all.

585
00:21:29.371 --> 00:21:32.208
Why don't we call you a Lyft?

586
00:21:32.291 --> 00:21:33.542
What is that?

587
00:21:33.626 --> 00:21:34.877
It's like a taxi service.

588
00:21:34.960 --> 00:21:36.712
If you put your address
in here.

589
00:21:36.796 --> 00:21:39.131
a car will arrive in a few
minutes to bring you home.

590
00:21:39.215 --> 00:21:40.466
- Oh.
- My treat.

591
00:21:41.759 --> 00:21:45.763
That's very kind of you. truly.

592
00:21:45.846 --> 00:21:47.348
Perfect.

593
00:21:47.431 --> 00:21:49.391
OK. Olive. could you take
Mrs. Clymer out

594
00:21:49.475 --> 00:21:52.102
to the ambulance bay.
where Florian will be

595
00:21:52.186 --> 00:21:54.271
arriving in six minutes
in a white Toyota Camry?

596
00:21:54.355 --> 00:21:55.481
You bet.

597
00:21:55.564 --> 00:21:56.857
Thank you.

598
00:21:56.941 --> 00:21:58.984
I could use some good karma.

599
00:21:59.068 --> 00:22:00.778
OK.

600
00:22:03.614 --> 00:22:05.825
Oh. uh. hey.

601
00:22:07.409 --> 00:22:08.702
Relax. buddy.

602
00:22:08.786 --> 00:22:10.538
It's Advil.

603
00:22:10.621 --> 00:22:12.832
No. I didn't think you were--

604
00:22:14.250 --> 00:22:15.918
Headache?

605
00:22:16.001 --> 00:22:18.963
Uh. I tweaked my back
a little

606
00:22:19.046 --> 00:22:21.799
lifting that overheated kid.

607
00:22:21.882 --> 00:22:23.133
I guess I should get used to

608
00:22:23.217 --> 00:22:25.886
playing through the pain
again. huh?

609
00:22:25.970 --> 00:22:28.347
You look like you got into
shape since I saw you last.

610
00:22:28.430 --> 00:22:30.307
Didn't peg you as a gym guy.

611
00:22:30.391 --> 00:22:31.725
Oh. no.

612
00:22:31.809 --> 00:22:34.520
I'm maybe more of a barn guy.

613
00:22:34.603 --> 00:22:37.565
I'm helping out a friend
on the farm. so...

614
00:22:39.233 --> 00:22:40.276
Nice.

615
00:22:40.359 --> 00:22:41.986
I'm picturing "Babe."

616
00:22:42.069 --> 00:22:43.779
except instead of
Farmer Hoggett. it's you.

617
00:22:43.863 --> 00:22:45.155
And instead of a pig--

618
00:22:45.239 --> 00:22:47.032
Can you cut the shit?

619
00:22:48.659 --> 00:22:49.952
Excuse me?

620
00:22:50.035 --> 00:22:52.204
The sarcasm thing.
the--the--the--

621
00:22:52.288 --> 00:22:53.956
the little buddy routine.
like--like--like.

622
00:22:54.039 --> 00:22:55.833
you're what. you're
the Skipper. I'm Gilligan?

623
00:22:55.916 --> 00:22:57.751
Dude. you're not the Skipper.

624
00:22:57.835 --> 00:23:00.004
I know I'm not the Skipper.
Robby is the Skipper.

625
00:23:00.087 --> 00:23:02.131
No. Robby is the Professor.
Dana's the Skipper.

626
00:23:02.214 --> 00:23:03.674
OK. somebody's watched
a lot of Nick at Nite.

627
00:23:03.757 --> 00:23:06.093
So who am I?

628
00:23:06.176 --> 00:23:08.262
Play whatever part you like.

629
00:23:08.345 --> 00:23:10.556
Just don't pick mine for me.

630
00:23:12.141 --> 00:23:13.434
OK.

631
00:23:13.517 --> 00:23:15.477
OK. that's fair.

632
00:23:15.561 --> 00:23:17.146
You got it.

633
00:23:17.229 --> 00:23:19.356
Thank you.

634
00:23:19.440 --> 00:23:21.775
You headed home?

635
00:23:21.859 --> 00:23:24.528
Uh. no. I'm waiting on Robby.

636
00:23:24.612 --> 00:23:26.322
He asked me to house-sit
while he's gone.

637
00:23:26.405 --> 00:23:29.158
So I'm waiting for the keys.
the alarm code.

638
00:23:30.576 --> 00:23:31.911
Nice. Nice.

639
00:23:31.994 --> 00:23:33.787
Yeah. I've--
I've seen his place.

640
00:23:33.871 --> 00:23:36.081
You're in for a sweet setup.

641
00:23:36.165 --> 00:23:38.167
Cool.

642
00:23:38.250 --> 00:23:42.004
I'm sorry if I came across
a little strong.

643
00:23:42.087 --> 00:23:44.340
Don't apologize
for standing up for yourself.

644
00:23:44.423 --> 00:23:46.342
It's a healthy habit.

645
00:23:48.385 --> 00:23:50.179
You know. I really don't
need to see this again.

646
00:23:50.262 --> 00:23:51.680
No. this is my favorite part.

647
00:23:53.307 --> 00:23:54.266
My hand's starting to cramp.

648
00:23:54.350 --> 00:23:55.517
We gotta be done soon.

649
00:23:55.601 --> 00:23:57.269
Oh. you can be done now.

650
00:23:57.353 --> 00:24:00.314
But if you want to the hospital
to cover you. last one.

651
00:24:05.986 --> 00:24:09.031
Hey. Robby.
It was an accident. man.

652
00:24:09.114 --> 00:24:10.574
What are you talking about?

653
00:24:10.658 --> 00:24:12.701
Your bike.

654
00:24:20.626 --> 00:24:23.087
Son of a bitch.

655
00:24:23.170 --> 00:24:25.881
Oh. motherfucker!

656
00:24:27.383 --> 00:24:29.343
Robby. GSW to the head.

657
00:24:29.426 --> 00:24:30.636
Somebody hit my bike.

658
00:24:30.719 --> 00:24:32.221
Dude. that sucks.

659
00:24:32.304 --> 00:24:33.722
Is it still rideable?

660
00:24:35.057 --> 00:24:36.600
It better be.

661
00:24:36.684 --> 00:24:38.852
Elbridge Gerry. 25.
stable with good vitals.

662
00:24:38.936 --> 00:24:40.437
Of thee I sing

663
00:24:40.521 --> 00:24:42.022
Was shooting his
.22 caliber pistol in the air

664
00:24:42.106 --> 00:24:43.524
with an aluminum pot
on his head for protection.

665
00:24:43.607 --> 00:24:44.858
Didn't work.

666
00:24:44.942 --> 00:24:46.235
He's had about a quart
of Seagrams 7

667
00:24:46.318 --> 00:24:47.528
and will probably light up
a tox screen

668
00:24:47.611 --> 00:24:49.863
like a Roman candle.

669
00:24:49.947 --> 00:24:52.449
We start fucking

670
00:24:52.533 --> 00:24:53.909
Real wordsmith.

671
00:24:53.993 --> 00:24:55.327
Entry wound
in the frontal scalp.

672
00:24:55.411 --> 00:24:56.662
seems to have tracked down
the forehead.

673
00:24:56.745 --> 00:24:57.788
As alert and oriented
as you can be

674
00:24:57.871 --> 00:24:59.039
after multiple bong hits.

675
00:24:59.123 --> 00:25:00.499
Got vital satting 98
on room air.

676
00:25:00.582 --> 00:25:01.834
- Sorry. Robby.
- Don't you fucking leave.

677
00:25:01.917 --> 00:25:02.835
- I can explain.
- I will be right back.

678
00:25:02.918 --> 00:25:03.836
What's this?

679
00:25:03.919 --> 00:25:05.295
Trauma 2.

680
00:25:05.379 --> 00:25:06.714
Low velocity GSW to the head.

681
00:25:06.797 --> 00:25:08.132
seems to have
remained extracranial.

682
00:25:08.215 --> 00:25:09.717
Lucky guy.

683
00:25:09.800 --> 00:25:13.846
Gloria. Gloria.
here's a dollar!

684
00:25:13.929 --> 00:25:16.390
After a fireworks
explosion resulting

685
00:25:16.473 --> 00:25:18.767
in the loss of two fingers.

686
00:25:18.851 --> 00:25:20.936
Ooh. that sounds nasty.

687
00:25:21.020 --> 00:25:23.605
Yeah. that was a sad one.

688
00:25:23.689 --> 00:25:24.982
Parents were deported.

689
00:25:25.065 --> 00:25:27.401
Big sister works
a full-time job

690
00:25:27.484 --> 00:25:28.944
and is the sole caregiver.

691
00:25:29.028 --> 00:25:30.612
Been there. done that.

692
00:25:30.696 --> 00:25:32.406
Your parents were deported?

693
00:25:32.489 --> 00:25:34.199
Oh. no.
I thought she said departed.

694
00:25:35.868 --> 00:25:37.661
Did either of you guys work on

695
00:25:37.745 --> 00:25:40.497
the Revolutionary War
reenactors earlier?

696
00:25:40.581 --> 00:25:43.208
Why. you didn't think you
could pull off a tricorn hat?

697
00:25:43.292 --> 00:25:46.086
Maybe.

698
00:25:46.170 --> 00:25:47.713
I've always loved history.

699
00:25:47.796 --> 00:25:51.759
and Colonial Williamsburg
was my favorite school trip.

700
00:25:51.842 --> 00:25:53.427
And. you know.
there's always the Ren Faire.

701
00:25:53.510 --> 00:25:55.846
but that's just once a year.

702
00:25:55.929 --> 00:25:58.140
How often do you think
the reenactors get together?

703
00:25:59.850 --> 00:26:01.560
I don't know. No.

704
00:26:01.643 --> 00:26:03.437
You should definitely
look into that.

705
00:26:03.520 --> 00:26:04.688
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

706
00:26:04.772 --> 00:26:05.981
OK.

707
00:26:15.991 --> 00:26:18.118
Deep-throated husky
with a touch of bitch.

708
00:26:18.202 --> 00:26:19.578
That's her tune.

709
00:26:19.661 --> 00:26:20.913
That's what I thought.
but you're the expert.

710
00:26:20.996 --> 00:26:22.539
I just needed to make sure.

711
00:26:23.999 --> 00:26:25.709
I was going through
Billings once.

712
00:26:25.793 --> 00:26:29.296
Cop saw my colors.
jacked me up.

713
00:26:29.379 --> 00:26:30.714
kept me overnight.

714
00:26:30.798 --> 00:26:34.384
They threw my sweetheart
in the impound yard.

715
00:26:34.468 --> 00:26:36.261
They claimed
someone backed into it.

716
00:26:36.345 --> 00:26:39.473
but you could see where they
took their hammer to it. man.

717
00:26:39.556 --> 00:26:40.933
You gotta be careful out there.

718
00:26:41.016 --> 00:26:42.267
This is all pretty minor.
though. right?

719
00:26:42.351 --> 00:26:44.561
Yeah. shit.
this is just cosmetic.

720
00:26:44.645 --> 00:26:47.064
Bring it in tomorrow.
and we'll get Bonnie right.

721
00:26:47.147 --> 00:26:48.774
Well. this will bend back.
This will tighten up.

722
00:26:48.857 --> 00:26:50.484
- I can do all that myself.
- Jesus. let me do it.

723
00:26:50.567 --> 00:26:51.735
- There's no charge.
- What?

724
00:26:51.819 --> 00:26:53.112
You don't owe me anything.
except

725
00:26:53.195 --> 00:26:55.614
take care of yourself
while I'm gone.

726
00:26:55.697 --> 00:26:57.491
Boy. this record
never stops. huh?

727
00:26:57.574 --> 00:27:00.369
Nah. it's dance
till you drop!

728
00:27:00.452 --> 00:27:01.870
Then what?

729
00:27:01.954 --> 00:27:03.956
Teach the kids the steps
before you do.

730
00:27:04.039 --> 00:27:05.332
And then what?

731
00:27:05.415 --> 00:27:06.834
Hope they make it
farther than you.

732
00:27:06.917 --> 00:27:08.460
Hey. Robby.
you're coming or going?

733
00:27:08.544 --> 00:27:10.254
I'm going. pretty soon.
What have you got here?

734
00:27:10.337 --> 00:27:13.173
Lyman Paine. 53. single MVC.

735
00:27:13.257 --> 00:27:14.341
Drove into a telephone pole.

736
00:27:14.424 --> 00:27:15.634
Passenger space intrusion?

737
00:27:15.717 --> 00:27:16.760
No. head on.

738
00:27:16.844 --> 00:27:17.761
Intoxicated?

739
00:27:17.845 --> 00:27:19.721
No ETOH on his breath.

740
00:27:19.805 --> 00:27:21.515
Either syncope. seizure.

741
00:27:21.598 --> 00:27:24.017
or he just fell asleep
at the wheel.

742
00:27:24.101 --> 00:27:26.061
Airbag deployed.
unconscious at the scene.

743
00:27:26.145 --> 00:27:27.062
but he's waking up.

744
00:27:27.146 --> 00:27:28.564
BP 140 over 80.

745
00:27:28.647 --> 00:27:30.357
pulse 120. pulse ox 98.

746
00:27:30.440 --> 00:27:31.608
no obvious injuries.

747
00:27:31.692 --> 00:27:32.609
Why don't you guys
head on in?

748
00:27:32.693 --> 00:27:33.819
I'll meet you in a minute.

749
00:27:38.615 --> 00:27:41.326
Well. hey. buddy.
I guess this is it.

750
00:27:41.410 --> 00:27:43.203
Make those appointments
next week. you know?

751
00:27:43.287 --> 00:27:45.330
I'll call you from the road
to make sure you do.

752
00:27:45.414 --> 00:27:46.999
- Don't do that. man.
- What?

753
00:27:47.082 --> 00:27:48.959
Don't shine me on.

754
00:27:49.042 --> 00:27:50.919
I'm not.

755
00:27:51.003 --> 00:27:52.379
Jesus.

756
00:27:52.462 --> 00:27:54.173
I get it.

757
00:27:54.256 --> 00:27:57.176
Hard place to leave.
a harder place to stay.

758
00:27:58.886 --> 00:28:00.012
Yeah.

759
00:28:02.431 --> 00:28:05.142
Look. I'm not ready
to say goodbye yet.

760
00:28:05.225 --> 00:28:08.645
So go do what you gotta do.
and I'll get some tools

761
00:28:08.729 --> 00:28:11.023
from the truck
and see if I can't make

762
00:28:11.106 --> 00:28:13.233
Bonnie smile again for you.

763
00:28:16.904 --> 00:28:18.155
OK.

764
00:28:18.238 --> 00:28:19.823
OK. then.

765
00:28:26.872 --> 00:28:29.208
Robby. man. I'm so sorry.
We've been on for 14 straight.

766
00:28:29.291 --> 00:28:30.834
- I thought I cleared it.
- It's all right.

767
00:28:30.918 --> 00:28:32.127
Honestly. I feel terrible.

768
00:28:32.211 --> 00:28:33.962
No real harm done.

769
00:28:34.046 --> 00:28:35.756
I was bound to nick it up
on the road anyway.

770
00:28:35.839 --> 00:28:39.051
First blood drawn.
it's a good omen really.

771
00:28:39.134 --> 00:28:40.510
Thought he'd be more pissed.

772
00:28:40.594 --> 00:28:42.554
I thought you might
get punched.

773
00:28:42.638 --> 00:28:44.056
Chest and belly look good.

774
00:28:44.139 --> 00:28:45.390
Let me drag Neurosurgery
down here to deal with

775
00:28:45.474 --> 00:28:46.600
the C-spine before I go.

776
00:28:46.683 --> 00:28:49.102
- You off?
- Yep. an hour ago.

777
00:28:49.186 --> 00:28:51.021
- Can't you tell?
- How you doing. sir?

778
00:28:51.104 --> 00:28:53.732
Actually. not too good.

779
00:28:53.815 --> 00:28:55.067
The tingling is getting worse.

780
00:28:55.150 --> 00:28:56.735
It's in both my arms now.

781
00:28:56.818 --> 00:28:58.362
